When `uv sync` fails with "missing library" errors:

| Python Package | Linux Libs | Darwin Libs |
|----------------|------------|-------------|
| `numpy`, `scipy` | `blas`, `lapack` | Same |
| `cryptography` | `openssl`, `libffi` | Same + `Security` framework |
| `lxml` | `libxml2`, `libxslt` | Same |
| `pillow` | `libjpeg`, `zlib` | Same |
| `psycopg2` | `postgresql` | Same |

Find missing libs: `nix-locate -w libfoo.so`

## Common Mistakes

| ❌ Wrong | Why It Breaks | ✅ Right |
|---------|---------------|---------|
| `import <nixpkgs>` in shell.nix | Impure, different nixpkgs per machine | Use flakes with locked inputs |
| `python3.withPackages (ps: [ps.requests])` | Mixes Nix and Python package management | Use `uv add requests` |
| `shellHook = "uv venv && uv sync"` | Creates new venv on every `nix develop` | Check `if [ ! -d .venv ]` first |
| Hardcoded `python311` | Prevents upgrades | Use latest stable (`python313`) |
| `buildInputs = [pkgs.python313]` | Wrong attribute for devShell | Use `packages = [pkgs.python313]` |

## Verification

```bash
nix flake check                # Validate flake syntax
nix develop                    # Enter shell
python --version               # Should match flake.nix version
uv --version                   # Should be available
python -c "import requests"    # Verify deps installed
```
